Product Description

Journey to Middle-earth's most enchanting corner with the LEGO Icons The Lord of the Rings: The Shire (10354) for adults ages 18 and up. This premium movie memorabilia set transports Middle-earth's most beloved location into your home through extraordinary attention to detail. Adult builders can construct Bilbo Baggins' iconic hobbit hole complete with round door, cozy interior rooms, and the lush Shire landscape that captured hearts worldwide. As you build, discover interactive features like Gandalf's fireworks display, the dragon firework that transforms into The One Ring, and intricate hobbit hole furnishings down to Bilbo's study and pantry. The set includes 9 detailed minifigures from the beloved films, bringing the magic of Bilbo's unexpected journey to life. The completed model doubles as stunning home or office decor that celebrates Tolkien's timeless world, or combine with other LEGO Icons Lord of the Rings building sets (each sold separately) to expand your Middle-earth collection. A perfect gift for Lord of the Rings fans and collectors , this premium building set offers a creative challenge that honors the magic of the film franchise. For an enhanced building experience, the LEGO Builder app provides helpful 3D viewing tools and progress tracking. Contains 2,017 pieces.

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Amazon Customer
    5 out of 5 stars
    Detailed set / sections are bagged to help keep everything organized
    This is a set for the Lego collector, in my opinion. Both the price point ( $269 at the time of this review ) and the detailed complex build, seem to be geared towards adults. The recommended age of 18 & up backs up my thought process on that aspect of this item. All the parts are bagged. The bags are labeled and this allows the user to build one section at a time without mixing up parts or having over two thousand pieces laying around loose. It is well made with customized Lego parts and very detailed instructions. This is not a Lego set designed to what I would term - use your own creativity and build something unique and original. This is a follow step by step and recreate the design shown on the box. This product in my opinion is pricy but I will assume if someone is considering this, they are comfortable with the prices of these large Lego sets and they see the value in it. Comparing it to other Lego sets in this price point, I think it is a good value. I recommend this for anyone who either enjoys the adult geared Lego kits or Lord of the Rings or both. In my opinion, the age recommendation is relative to the patience and nature of the person choosing this …I know many 10-12 year olds who love this kind of challenge and choose these kits when their birthday or Christmas budget allows. I also know many 25 year olds that would quickly become frustrated and not enjoy this type of puzzle. My suggestion would be to choose at your own digression and based on possible prior experience with these large adult geared Lego sets. If choosing for under 18, adult guidance is recommended to get things going the right direction.

    • JohnnyB
      4.0 out of 5 stars No missing pieces
      Reviewed in the United States on July 22, 2025
      Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
      This "LEGO Icons The Lord of The Rings: 2,017pcs. The Shire Building Set 10354, Ages 18+" came packaged in the standard printed LEGO branded box seen in the listing picture. The parts came packaged in 16 numbered plastic bags and one unlabeled plastic bag. The cloth-like material pieces (tent roof, banner, cape) were packaged in a brown envelope to keep them from getting smashed and/or creased. The 3 instruction manuals and 1 small sticker sheet were also packaged in a brown paper bag/enelope for protection. The numbered bags and clear instructions made for a trouble free build. There were no missing pieces. Based on the pictures, the banner is printed upside-down, with the larger holes on the bottom rather than the top. This causes the banner to sit up a bit higher than it was designed to. Not sure if this is an error in all of these sets, or just the one I got. There are a lot of details in this set, but not a lot of play features. The amount of pieces that are easily knocked off when played with and the sometimes boring build is likely the reason for the 18+ age rating. As an adult builder this set was fairly easy to build and I appreciate all of the details and relevant minifigures.
